description.narrative: Despite social, health and operational challenges caused by COVID-19 in the first half of the year, UNICEF managed to support more than 20,000 children affected by conflict to complete their education in the 2019-2020 school year. More than 6,000 boys and girls completed non-formal primary and middle school education. Support for upstream and policy work continued and UNICEF stepped up its Education in Emergency coordination work to ensure that children in conflict-affected areas were not left behind, including in COVID-19 response and recovery work. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/07/2020
